Paper: hep-th/9704176

Date: 1997-04-24

Title: Screening in three-dimensional QED

Authors: E. Abdalla and R. Banerjee

Comments: 7 pages, one figure, latex file, version to appear in Physical Review

LettersJournal-ref: Phys.Rev.Lett. 80 (1998) 238-240

We compute the quark-antiquark potential in three dimensional massive QuantumElectrodynamics. The result indicates that screening prevails for large quarkmasses, contrary to the classical expectations. The classical result isreproduced for small separation of the quarks.